# When adding a new modifier
* `src/modifiers`
  * Update `/definitions` - usually two classes per modifier, one being the modifier class and the other the modifier object class
  * Register modifiers in `CustomModifiersManager`
  * For Combat Modifiers, expand `patchCombatModifiersReset` with those modifiers, to ensure they don't have a value of `undefined`
  * Register method patches in `CustomModifiersManager`
* `src/translation`
  * Add translation entries for the new modifiers (for every language, even if it's just english for all of them)
* `src/compatibility`
  * Add "Tiny Icons" definitions for the new modifiers
* `src/components`
  * **If** you added a whole new monster type, add it to the lists displayed in the overview